{"url": "https://www.ics.uci.edu/~kobsa/courses/ICS104/course-notes/gdl-color-blindness.htm", "content": "<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC \"-//w3c//dtd html 4.0 transitional//en\">\n<html>\n<head>\n  <meta http-equiv=\"Content-Type\"\n content=\"text/html; charset=iso-8859-1\">\n  <meta name=\"GENERATOR\"\n content=\"Mozilla/4.72 (Macintosh; I; PPC) [Netscape]\">\n  <title>Color deficiencies, adaptation problems</title>\n</head>\n<body bgcolor=\"#ffffff\">\n<font face=\"Arial,Helvetica\"><font size=\"6\"><font size=\"7\">Color\ndeficiencies, adaptation problems<br>\n</font></font></font> <br>\n<table bgcolor=\"#ffffff\" border=\"1\" bordercolor=\"#ffffff\" height=\"320\"\n width=\"770\">\n  <tbody>\n    <tr>\n      <td height=\"329\" width=\"553\">\n      <p><font face=\"Arial,Helvetica\"><font face=\"Arial,Helvetica\"><font\n size=\"6\">1. Color deficiencies</font></font></font> </p>\n      <p><font face=\"Arial,Helvetica\"><font size=\"5\">8% of white U.S.\nmales are red/green blind<br>\n      </font></font> </p>\n      <p><font face=\"Arial,Helvetica\"><font size=\"5\">(less in other\nraces; white females: 0.5%)<br>\n      </font><font face=\"Arial,Helvetica\"><font size=\"5\">these colors\nappear medium-gray</font></font><font size=\"5\"> </font></font> </p>\n      <p><font face=\"Monotype Sorts\"><font size=\"+3\">*</font></font><font\n size=\"5\"><span style=\"font-family: Monotype Sorts;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\n      </span><font face=\"Arial,Helvetica\">Design for monochrome first,\nand add <br>\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; color as a</font></font> <font size=\"5\"><i><font\n face=\"Arial,Helvetica\"> &nbsp;</font></i><font face=\"Arial,Helvetica\"><i>redundant</i>\ndevice.</font></font> <font size=\"5\"><br>\n      <font face=\"Arial,Helvetica\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; If\nthis is not (fully) possible, objects<br>\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; should not only be</font></font> <font\n face=\"Arial,Helvetica\" size=\"5\">distinguished<br>\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; by their amount of red or green.</font> <font\n size=\"5\"><br>\n      </font> </p>\n      </td>\n      <td height=\"329\" width=\"286\"><img src=\"color-blindness-model.jpg\"\n height=\"300\" width=\"193\"></td>\n    </tr>\n  </tbody>\n</table>\n<p><font face=\"Arial,Helvetica\"><font face=\"Arial,Helvetica\"><font\n size=\"+3\">2. Adaptation problems</font></font></font> </p>\n<p><font face=\"Arial,Helvetica\"><font size=\"5\">Colors have different\nwavelengths, ranging from red (610nm) to orange, yellow,<br>\ngreen, blue and violett (380nm). Pupils must refocus when colors change.</font></font>\n</p>\n<p><font face=\"Monotype Sorts\"><font size=\"+3\">*</font></font><font\n size=\"5\"><span style=\"font-family: Monotype Sorts;\">&nbsp; &nbsp; </span><font\n face=\"Arial,Helvetica\">When users' eyes must constantly switch between\nobjects of</font></font> <font size=\"5\"><br>\n<font face=\"Arial,Helvetica\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; different\ncolor, avoid combinations of colors that differ strongly</font></font> <font\n size=\"5\"><br>\n<font face=\"Arial,Helvetica\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; in their\nwavelengths (this hold particularly true for elderly users).</font></font>\n</p>\n</body>\n</html>\n", "encoding": "ascii"}